Sentencas: A cobalt-free perovskite oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-delta (BSFC) is employed as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Cobalt-free oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Symmetrical electrochemical cell with the configuration of BSFC-BZCY/BZCY/BSFC-BZCY is applied for the impedance study.
Titulo: Cobalt-free oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: The single cell, consisting of BSFC-BZCY/BZCY/NiO-BZCY structure, is assembled and tested from 600 to 700 degrees C with humidified hydrogen (similar to 3% H2O) as the fuel and the static air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Cobalt-free oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: A maximum power density of 430 mW cm(-2) is obtained at 700 degrees C for the single cell.
Titulo: Cobalt-free oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Long-term stability of the BSFC-BZCY/BZCY/NiO-BZCY single cell at 600 degrees C for 40 h has also been studied.
Titulo: Cobalt-free oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Preliminary results demonstrat that cobalt-free oxide BSFC is a very promising cathode for application in proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Cobalt-free oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell cathode
